  "prompt": "When is surge pricing on Uber generally in effect in Sarasota and how high does it go?",
  "response": "Surge pricing on Uber typically comes into effect during periods of high demand and low supply of available drivers. In Sarasota, this can often occur during:\n\n1. Special events or large gatherings (such as sports games, concerts, festivals, etc.)\n2. Holidays and holiday weekends.\n3. Peak travel times, such as Friday and Saturday nights.\n4. Bad weather conditions.\n\nThe extent of surge pricing varies, but it can sometimes double or even triple the usual fare depending on the specific circumstances and the level of demand at the time. Prices could multiply in some extreme cases, though those are less common. To get the most accurate information, it's advisable to check the Uber app during different times and conditions.",
